Sara McNeely
March 17 at 6:07 PM ·

Your friendly neighborhood art teacher here, with an assignment for our community. Will you help me send our kids on an Easter egg hunt?! Cut out and decorate an egg to hang in your window. You could cut it out of paper, cardboard, whatever you have and decorate it any way you’d like. Then hang it in a street side window so anyone outside can see it. When the kids are out for walks or riding their bikes, they can “hunt” for eggs around town! Go for a family walk and see who can find the most, each pick a color and see who can find the most eggs of their color, see who can spot the biggest egg.... who’s going to egg their house with me?!

post_text: Thank you to all who supported our bond referendum for the addition to our school. The referendum (unofficially) passed and we will move forward with the process of preparing for construction to begin. It is so fulfilling to live in a community that supports our students and school, as well as each of the communities in our school district that provide support to Enderlin Area School. We cannot thank you enough. Not just for passing this referendum, but for all that you do to support our students and school. Thank you!
